children.subject: Just a point of information, CS 168 is only offered in fall, so you might have to rework your schedule a bit to account for that.

A few points:

- Your Spring 2018 schedule seems quite a high workload to me.

- CS 168 is only offered in Fall.

- EECS 127 is (usually) only offered in Spring.

history.content:
Would it be possible to get some thoughts on the following course load for the next few semesters? I've already taken CS 61A/B, EE 16A/B and Math 53/54. Currently enrolled in CS61C and CS70. 

Spring 2018: CS 170, EECS 126, CS 186

Fall 2018: CS 188, CS 189, EECS 127

Spring 2019: CS 161, CS 162, CS 168

My first priority is whether I can balance out this course load more, but I would appreciate advice on whether these classes complement each other well and whether I'm taking them at the optimal time (because of professors, curriculum, etc). If it helps, I'm interested in the ML route, which is why I have 126/127/189 lined up earlier.

Thanks in advance!
